==English==

===Etymology===
First attested in the 1530s. From {{der|en|fr|abusif}}, from {{der|en|la|abūsīvus}},<ref name=RHD>{{R:RHCD|page=6}}</ref> from {{m|la|abusus}} + {{m|la|-ivus||-ive}}.<ref name=WI3>{{R:MW3 1976|page=8}}</ref> Equivalent to {{suffix|abuse|ive|lang=en}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/əˈbjuː.sɪv/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/əˈbju.sɪv/|/əˈbju.zɪv/|lang=en}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Prone to treat someone badly by coarse, [[insulting]] words or other maltreatment; [[vituperative]]; [[reproachful]]; [[scurrilous]]. {{defdate|First attested in the early 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
#* {{quote-book|passage=An '''abusive''' lampoon.|author=[[w:Samuel Johnson|Samuel Johnson]]|title=A dictionary of the English language}}
